The council shall be composed of thirteen (13) voting members and two (2) nonvoting ex officio members as follows:
The Commissioner of Agriculture or his or her designee;
The state veterinarian or his or her designee;
One (1) representative of the University of Kentucky College of Agriculture Equine Initiative to be designated by the dean of the University of Kentucky College of Agriculture;
One (1) representative of the University of Louisville Equine Industry Program to be designated by the dean of the College of Business;
One (1) representative of equine education programs chosen by Morehead State University, Murray State University, or Western Kentucky University on a rotating basis at the pleasure of the university to serve a one (1) year term;
The executive director of the University of Kentucky Livestock Disease Diagnostic Center, or his or her designee, or the executive director of the Murray State University Breathitt Veterinary Center, or his or her designee, who shall serve one (1) year terms on a rotating basis;
One (1) representative of the Kentucky Farm Bureau Federation with an interest in equine issues;
One (1) veterinarian representing the Kentucky Equine Health and Welfare Alliance Inc.;
One (1) member representing the Kentucky Veterinary Medical Association;
One (1) member to be appointed by the Governor from a list of three (3) nominees submitted by the Kentucky Horse Council;
One (1) member representing organized horse rescue entities to be selected by the Governor from a listing of those who apply for membership on the council;
Two (2) members at large who live in diverse regions of the state to be appointed by the Governor. Each member at large shall primarily represent one (1) of the following:
Equine breeders and owners; and
Agricultural interests;
The chair of the Senate Standing Committee on Agriculture, who shall serve as a nonvoting ex officio member; and
The chair of the House Standing Committee on Agriculture and Small Business, who shall serve as a nonvoting ex officio member.
